WEBVTT

00:03.171 --> 00:05.139
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

00:05.173 --> 00:08.909
You can't run from me
any longer.

00:08.942 --> 00:11.312
[ Breathing heavily ]

00:11.345 --> 00:14.848
**

00:14.882 --> 00:18.486
I know you're in here, killer!

00:18.519 --> 00:20.421
**

00:20.454 --> 00:23.757
[ Metal scrapes ]

00:23.791 --> 00:27.395
**

00:27.428 --> 00:29.730
This is the end.

00:29.763 --> 00:32.433
I spent all this time
looking for you,

00:32.466 --> 00:34.902
and you are behind this door.

00:34.935 --> 00:37.938
**

00:37.971 --> 00:39.407
Now what?

00:39.440 --> 00:41.509
[ Groans ]

00:41.542 --> 00:43.511
Still don't know
who the killer is?

00:43.544 --> 00:44.878
No!

00:44.912 --> 00:47.081
I can't finish "A Case
of a Knife to the Brain"

00:47.115 --> 00:49.850
if I don't know who put
that knife in that brain.

00:49.883 --> 00:51.285
Sounds like
writer's block.

00:51.319 --> 00:52.686
How do you know that term?

00:52.720 --> 00:54.622
I had writer's block
when I was drafting

00:54.655 --> 00:56.790
the new HOA regulations.

00:56.824 --> 00:59.760
I could not find a synonym
for the word "forbidden."

00:59.793 --> 01:00.794
"Banned."

01:00.828 --> 01:03.131
I went with "no-no."

01:03.164 --> 01:04.965
Had to dumb it down
for Carol-Joan.

01:04.998 --> 01:06.267
That's true.

01:06.300 --> 01:08.769
[ Blows ]

01:08.802 --> 01:11.139
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:11.172 --> 01:12.306
* Fresh off the boat

01:12.340 --> 01:14.041
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

01:14.074 --> 01:16.310
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

01:16.344 --> 01:17.611
* Fresh off the boat

01:17.645 --> 01:19.947
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

01:19.980 --> 01:21.415
* But I know where I'm goin'

01:21.449 --> 01:24.152
* I'm fresh off the boat

01:24.185 --> 01:27.087
I've written myself
into a corner, Louis.

01:27.121 --> 01:28.789
This crime is too perfect.
I'm sure it's --

01:28.822 --> 01:31.625
If Jennifer Hong can't solve
these murders, then who can?

01:31.659 --> 01:34.262
She is the ultimate
detective -- beautiful.

01:34.295 --> 01:35.996
Smart. Observant.

01:36.029 --> 01:36.997
Beautiful.

01:37.030 --> 01:38.499
Maybe you just need
a break.

01:38.532 --> 01:40.301
When I was updating
the menus at Cattleman's,

01:40.334 --> 01:41.502
I got stuck on salads --

01:41.535 --> 01:44.605
Not to mention,
the coffee maker is broken!

01:44.638 --> 01:46.807
How am I supposed to write
without coffee?

01:46.840 --> 01:49.109
Mm, our friend the carrot
provides natural energy.

01:49.143 --> 01:51.445
Please, do not push
your vegetable agenda on me.

01:51.479 --> 01:53.781
And this coffee-maker manual
was no help!

01:53.814 --> 01:56.284
26 languages,
and all it talks about

01:56.317 --> 01:59.187
is how to set
the digital clock.

01:59.220 --> 02:00.921
The Mandarin was accurate,
though.

02:00.954 --> 02:03.524
I know the writing's
been hard, but keep at it.

02:03.557 --> 02:04.592
You'll figure it out.

02:04.625 --> 02:06.093
What if I can't?

02:06.126 --> 02:07.461
Oh, you're being
too hard on yourself.

02:07.495 --> 02:09.029
Don't be
your own worst enemy.

02:09.062 --> 02:11.199
You're right.

02:11.232 --> 02:13.801
If Stephen King can trick
people into thinking

02:13.834 --> 02:17.538
a dog is interesting
for 300 pages, I can do this.

02:17.571 --> 02:19.273
**

02:19.307 --> 02:22.009
* Do you really wanna party
with me? *

02:22.042 --> 02:24.445
* Let me see
just what you got for me *

02:24.478 --> 02:26.714
* Put all your hands
where my eyes can see *

02:26.747 --> 02:29.016
* Straight buckwildin'
in the place to be *

02:29.049 --> 02:30.484
* If you really wanna party
with me *

02:30.518 --> 02:32.286
Now, that's how you break down
the apocalypse.

02:32.320 --> 02:35.689
May it never come so Busta
can keep rapping about it.

02:35.723 --> 02:37.558
I didn't even know
he put out a new record.

02:37.591 --> 02:39.026
That's what
we got Eddie for.

02:39.059 --> 02:42.230
I may not be able to tell you
where Canada is on the map,

02:42.263 --> 02:44.131
but I can tell you
the current Hip-Hop 100.

02:44.164 --> 02:45.299
Uhp!

02:45.333 --> 02:46.867
Usher just went up
a couple spots.

02:46.900 --> 02:48.669
Good for Ursh.

02:48.702 --> 02:50.471
Whose turn is it
to load a new CD?

02:50.504 --> 02:51.505
-Man...
-But my feet.

02:51.539 --> 02:52.506
I literally
just sat down.

02:52.540 --> 02:53.841
Well, it's not gonna be me.

02:53.874 --> 02:56.176
It's my room.
I stand up in it all the time.

02:56.210 --> 02:57.745
-Hey, hey!
-Our guy!

02:57.778 --> 02:59.046
What an entrance!
Brian!

02:59.079 --> 03:00.248
Change the CD, will ya?

03:00.281 --> 03:03.884
-I got up to pee, not work.
-[ Groans ]

03:03.917 --> 03:07.988
Gentlemen, our prayers
have been answered.

03:08.021 --> 03:09.490
Eddie: 300 discs?

03:09.523 --> 03:11.492
We'll never have to get up
to change the CD again.

03:11.525 --> 03:14.695
We just press "shuffle," and
it does all the work for us.

03:14.728 --> 03:17.365
-How much is it?
-$300.

03:17.398 --> 03:19.433
Only a dollar a disc.

03:19.467 --> 03:21.201
If we all go in,
it's just 60 bucks each.

03:21.235 --> 03:22.436
-All right.
-Yeah.

03:22.470 --> 03:23.504
-All right.
-Okay.

03:23.537 --> 03:24.938
Eddie, you sure
you're good for it?

03:24.972 --> 03:28.376
[ Scoffs ]
Are you questioning my stacks?

03:28.409 --> 03:30.444
Yeah.
I'm good for it.

03:30.478 --> 03:32.280
Hey, bros.

03:32.313 --> 03:33.447
Spot me 60 bucks
real quick.

03:33.481 --> 03:37.050
**

03:37.084 --> 03:39.420
Louis.
I've got big news.

03:39.453 --> 03:41.789
Someone ordered
the bison tartare. I knew it.

03:41.822 --> 03:43.123
I knew if we just kept it
on the menu,

03:43.156 --> 03:45.559
someone would eventually
have the courage to --
No.

03:45.593 --> 03:49.897
Kenny Rogers is visiting
Cattleman's Ranch this week.

03:49.930 --> 03:52.366
Ohh.

03:52.400 --> 03:53.901
Don't you lie to me,
Matthew Chestnut.

03:53.934 --> 03:55.269
Kenny always does
two tours a year --

03:55.303 --> 03:56.404
one musical, one business.

03:56.437 --> 03:57.738
I mean,
not that he has time

03:57.771 --> 03:59.540
to visit every one
of his restaurants.

03:59.573 --> 04:00.608
Of course
he can't visit them all.

04:00.641 --> 04:01.942
The man
runs a culinary empire.

04:01.975 --> 04:04.978
Exactly. He's only got time
to visit a select few.

04:05.012 --> 04:08.949
Ones that he finds, for
whatever reason, "excitin'."

04:08.982 --> 04:11.285
That's even better
than "exci-ting."

04:11.319 --> 04:12.620
That's cowboy joy.

04:12.653 --> 04:14.288
Whew!
[ Laughs ]

04:14.322 --> 04:18.091
**

04:18.125 --> 04:19.660
Oh, Emery.

04:19.693 --> 04:20.928
My son.

04:20.961 --> 04:23.497
So, when two leaders
meet for the first time,

04:23.531 --> 04:25.466
it is customary to have
an exchange of gifts.

04:25.499 --> 04:27.401
Which one
do you like more?

04:27.435 --> 04:29.637
This boutique pen
featuring a covered wagon

04:29.670 --> 04:31.405
traveling across
the American West.

04:31.439 --> 04:34.308
Or...an 8x10 sketch

04:34.342 --> 04:37.511
of a cow and chicken
riding motorcycles?

04:37.545 --> 04:39.580
Well, it is kind of hard
to wrap a pen

04:39.613 --> 04:41.014
without giving away
what it is.

04:41.048 --> 04:42.750
[ Chuckles ]
Not the way I wrap.

04:42.783 --> 04:43.951
I once wrapped a toaster

04:43.984 --> 04:45.786
that your mother thought
was diamond earrings.

04:45.819 --> 04:47.120
She was very disappointed.

04:47.154 --> 04:49.490
Do you want me to say
the pen?

04:49.523 --> 04:51.959
My son!
Mm.

04:51.992 --> 04:53.160
[ Scooter approaching ]

04:55.729 --> 04:56.830
Hmm.

04:57.831 --> 04:59.967
Jessica: Hey!
Where are you going?!

05:02.836 --> 05:04.037
Grandma Huang:
[ Scoffs ]

05:04.071 --> 05:06.474
Well, she was supposed
to play Amy Grant.

05:06.507 --> 05:08.542
So I could announce...

05:08.576 --> 05:11.545
that I finished my book!
[ Gasps ]

05:11.579 --> 05:13.981
Oh, wow! That's great!
I knew you would!

05:14.014 --> 05:15.949
I couldn't have done it
without your support.

05:15.983 --> 05:17.050
I can't wait to read it.

05:17.084 --> 05:18.519
You don't have to.

05:20.320 --> 05:22.155
Not sure
if you're asking me to --

05:22.189 --> 05:23.491
Read it all tonight?
Yes, I am.

05:23.524 --> 05:24.958
And while you're doing that,

05:24.992 --> 05:26.827
I'm just gonna ride
this creative high.

05:26.860 --> 05:28.462
I'm gonna craft
a complaint letter

05:28.496 --> 05:29.630
to the people at Mr. Coffee.

05:29.663 --> 05:31.031
Don't tell me I can't.

05:31.064 --> 05:32.733
Well, I'm kind of
in the middle of preparing

05:32.766 --> 05:34.835
for Kenny Rogers' first visit
to Cattleman's.

05:34.868 --> 05:37.037
You're finally
gonna meet Kenny.

05:37.070 --> 05:38.539
That's big.
I know!

05:38.572 --> 05:40.508
So would it be okay
if I read your book later?

05:40.541 --> 05:42.743
Oh, Louis. No.

05:45.613 --> 05:47.615
**

05:55.623 --> 05:57.625
**

06:03.931 --> 06:07.334
How am I only on page 9?!

06:07.367 --> 06:09.102
So many commas.

06:09.136 --> 06:11.705
[ Scoffs ]
The cleaning lady is a robot?

06:11.739 --> 06:13.273
What year is this?!

06:13.306 --> 06:16.109
Why is the police chief
suddenly twins?

06:16.143 --> 06:18.378
"It had all led here,

06:18.412 --> 06:21.782
the trail of so many knives
to so many brains.

06:21.815 --> 06:24.051
Jennifer Hong, ever beautiful,

06:24.084 --> 06:27.120
extended her ageless hand
to the doorknob."

06:27.154 --> 06:30.424
**

06:30.458 --> 06:32.125
[ Gasps ]

06:32.159 --> 06:34.127
"The killer was herself"?

06:34.161 --> 06:35.463
Right?!
Aaaah!

06:35.496 --> 06:37.330
That scary, huh?

06:38.398 --> 06:40.133
That ending
was thanks to you.

06:40.167 --> 06:43.804
I got the idea when you told me
not to be my own worst enemy.

06:43.837 --> 06:46.139
I did the opposite
of what you said.

06:46.173 --> 06:48.442
Oh.
Right. Right.

06:48.476 --> 06:49.810
So, what do you think?

06:51.244 --> 06:52.446
I love it.
[ Chuckles ]

06:52.480 --> 06:53.447
It was amazing!

06:53.481 --> 06:55.115
I know!

06:55.148 --> 06:57.417
I can't believe
I finished my novel!

06:57.451 --> 06:58.919
You did.
You finished it.

06:58.952 --> 07:00.488
It's all over.

07:00.521 --> 07:03.624
I feel like a runner
at the end of a marathon.

07:03.657 --> 07:05.926
Except words
are my miles.

07:05.959 --> 07:07.127
Oh.

07:07.160 --> 07:10.998
**

07:11.031 --> 07:14.301
[ Dramatic music plays ]

07:14.334 --> 07:17.137
More than 3,500 songs
inside a machine

07:17.170 --> 07:21.609
that's only 17 inches long by
8 inches wide by 19 inches deep.

07:21.642 --> 07:24.411
And she only weighs
20 pounds.

07:24.444 --> 07:25.813
-Crazy.
-Awesome.

07:25.846 --> 07:26.914
Technology.

07:26.947 --> 07:28.849
I loaded every one of my CDs
in here.

07:30.183 --> 07:32.986
[ CD player powering up ]

07:34.321 --> 07:35.689
Oh, look at it go.

07:37.124 --> 07:38.492
It's like a light show.

07:39.459 --> 07:41.028
My heart
is racing right now.

07:41.061 --> 07:44.164
[ Beeping ]

07:44.197 --> 07:49.603
[ Intro to "Circle of Life"
from "The Lion King" plays ]

07:49.637 --> 07:51.505
Yes!
Mufasa time!

07:51.539 --> 07:54.207
[ Music stops ]
You guys put
your "Lion King" CD in?

07:54.241 --> 07:55.676
We lent you
the money to buy it,

07:55.709 --> 07:57.545
so we figured
we'd take some slots.

07:57.578 --> 07:59.146
[ Switch clicks ]

07:59.179 --> 08:01.381
[ Music resumes ]

08:01.414 --> 08:02.482
[ Music stops ]

08:02.516 --> 08:04.151
You guys
don't get any slots.

08:04.184 --> 08:05.986
I-I don't know, Eddie.

08:06.019 --> 08:08.288
If they lent you money,
they kinda have a point.

08:08.321 --> 08:09.723
Now that I think about it...

08:09.757 --> 08:11.725
shouldn't we have
our share of the slots, too?

08:11.759 --> 08:14.194
Why would you need that?
You love my music.

08:14.227 --> 08:16.196
We do,
but it might be cool

08:16.229 --> 08:17.397
to throw some slow jams
in there.

08:17.430 --> 08:18.899
Okay, new plan.

08:18.932 --> 08:21.068
Next time,
we all bring our Case Logics.

08:21.101 --> 08:21.902
Yeah?
-Mm-hmm.

08:21.935 --> 08:22.736
-Yep.
-All right.

08:22.770 --> 08:24.004
What's going on here?

08:24.037 --> 08:27.808
I'm gonna bring all the CDs
I listen to when I lift.

08:27.841 --> 08:29.543
You could be a watch.

08:29.577 --> 08:31.845
You could be
a tightly packed tie.

08:31.879 --> 08:33.747
You could be
an ice-cream sandwich.

08:33.781 --> 08:37.350
Are you excited
to meet Kenny Rogers?
I am!

08:37.384 --> 08:38.652
I memorized all his songs

08:38.686 --> 08:40.721
in case he brings his guitar
and wants to jam.

08:40.754 --> 08:43.090
Great. You can do that
after you give him my novel

08:43.123 --> 08:45.492
so he can give it to his agent
and get it published!

08:45.525 --> 08:47.227
**

08:51.632 --> 08:53.200
W-Why would you want me
to give Kenny Rogers your book?

08:53.233 --> 08:55.569
He's a country singer/
restauranteur/underrated actor.

08:55.603 --> 08:58.205
Louis, I forgive you.

08:58.238 --> 08:59.506
It's not your fault
you weren't born

08:59.539 --> 09:00.774
with my detective mind.

09:00.808 --> 09:02.776
What are you saying?

09:02.810 --> 09:04.377
The fastest way
to get published

09:04.411 --> 09:06.113
is through someone
already in the business.

09:06.146 --> 09:09.049
So I did a little digging
on everyone we know.

09:09.082 --> 09:10.283
By the way, remind me
to tell you

09:10.317 --> 09:11.952
why Deidre can no longer
travel through Utah.

09:11.985 --> 09:15.623
And I discovered
that just last year,

09:15.656 --> 09:18.291
Kenny Rogers wrote
and published a book --

09:18.325 --> 09:20.527
"The Gift."

09:20.560 --> 09:24.297
He's an author,
just like me!

09:24.331 --> 09:25.532
Don't tell me.

09:25.565 --> 09:27.467
It's about the greatest gift
being literacy, right?

09:27.500 --> 09:28.969
I don't know.
I didn't read it.

09:29.002 --> 09:31.371
Anyway, with your
personal recommendation,

09:31.404 --> 09:33.974
there's no way
Kenny won't read my novel.

09:34.007 --> 09:35.743
Right.

09:35.776 --> 09:37.444
Sounds like a great idea.

09:37.477 --> 09:42.449
**

09:42.482 --> 09:43.784
Come on.

09:43.817 --> 09:45.118
Lemme see
what you're putting in there.

09:45.152 --> 09:48.021
Part of the experience
is the suspense.

09:50.523 --> 09:52.159
[ Whirring ]

09:52.192 --> 09:54.662
What a rush!
Who's it gonna be?!

09:54.695 --> 09:55.796
[ Click ]

09:55.829 --> 09:57.965
[ Enya's "Book of Days" plays ]

09:57.998 --> 09:59.466
Yes!

09:59.499 --> 10:01.134
Welcome to the party,
Enya!

10:01.168 --> 10:02.302
Are you kidding me
with this?

10:03.837 --> 10:04.805
[ Music stops ]

10:04.838 --> 10:06.006
-What are you doing?
-Come on!

10:06.039 --> 10:07.407
[ Fife playing ]

10:07.440 --> 10:09.142
Man: The waters of
the Delaware River ran cold.

10:09.176 --> 10:10.610
But the fire in George
Washington's eyes burned hot.

10:10.644 --> 10:12.412
My audio book
about the American Revolution!

10:12.445 --> 10:14.147
Get ready to learn, everyone.
It was the morning
of December 26th...

10:14.181 --> 10:15.582
Audio book?
This isn't even music!

10:15.615 --> 10:16.950
...when he led a column
of the Continental --

10:16.984 --> 10:18.251
Hey!
Ugh!

10:18.285 --> 10:19.486
[ High-pitched voice ]
They said...

10:19.519 --> 10:21.021
Man: "You belong in
the kitchen, Betsy Ross."

10:21.054 --> 10:22.289
And the kitchen is where I --

10:22.322 --> 10:23.957
[ Sighs ]
Screw this!

10:23.991 --> 10:26.126
I'm just gonna manually select
one of my CDs.

10:26.159 --> 10:27.294
No way!

10:27.327 --> 10:29.296
Who are you to control
what we listen to?

10:29.329 --> 10:32.165
Guys. I've always been
in charge of the music.

10:32.199 --> 10:34.534
Why would you want to listen
to this lame garbage?

10:34.567 --> 10:36.269
In Dave's defense,
Enya's voice

10:36.303 --> 10:38.138
has been known
to summon whales.

10:38.171 --> 10:40.140
Well, as long
as the CD player's in my room,

10:40.173 --> 10:41.709
we're not listening
to whale rock.

10:41.742 --> 10:43.476
Well, maybe we shouldn't
keep the CD player

10:43.510 --> 10:44.544
in your room, then.

10:44.577 --> 10:46.479
Brian:
We each own a portion of it.

10:46.513 --> 10:48.148
We can take turns
having it at our houses.

10:48.181 --> 10:50.117
Like the shared-custody
situation

10:50.150 --> 10:51.184
I'd like to have with my dad

10:51.218 --> 10:52.820
if we could ever find out
where he is.

10:52.853 --> 10:54.654
Eddie: Fine.

10:54.688 --> 10:56.556
Well, it's in my room now,
so I get it first.

10:56.589 --> 10:58.525
And I'm skipping over
whatever I want.

10:58.558 --> 10:59.727
-Come on!
-Stop it, Eddie.

10:59.760 --> 11:00.828
Young man:
What are you doing?

11:00.861 --> 11:02.195
I, for one, am not
just gonna sit here

11:02.229 --> 11:04.497
and watch you skip over
the founding of our nation!

11:04.531 --> 11:09.870
**

11:09.903 --> 11:11.504
[ Click ]

11:11.538 --> 11:13.140
* One day, one life *

11:13.173 --> 11:14.842
No!
[ Music stops ]

11:16.509 --> 11:18.511
Guys, her book is not good.

11:18.545 --> 11:19.913
But you told her
it wa good.

11:19.947 --> 11:21.548
Yeah, because I love her.

11:21.581 --> 11:23.717
But now that she's asked me
to recommend it to Kenny,

11:23.751 --> 11:24.918
it's
a totally different thing.

11:24.952 --> 11:26.987
I can't endorse something
I don't believe in.

11:27.020 --> 11:28.255
Oh, that's true.

11:28.288 --> 11:29.957
That's why I don't pet cats.

11:31.291 --> 11:33.226
Mm.

11:33.260 --> 11:34.427
Well, not to mention
the fact

11:34.461 --> 11:36.396
that nobody wants to meet
someone for the first time

11:36.429 --> 11:38.065
and ask for a huge favor.

11:38.098 --> 11:39.833
I think you should tell her
the truth.

11:39.867 --> 11:41.168
I mean,
Jessica can take it.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.270
She's given me
some pretty candid critiques

11:43.303 --> 11:44.437
over the years.
[ Chuckles ]

11:44.471 --> 11:45.939
My cooking
lacks discipline.

11:45.973 --> 11:47.775
The way I sign my name
suggests weakness.

11:47.808 --> 11:49.609
I laugh wrong.
I wear too much cologne.

11:49.642 --> 11:51.879
My dancing
comes across as arrogant.

11:51.912 --> 11:53.914
Oh, well, that's because
you point all the time, sweetie.

11:53.947 --> 11:57.785
Well, honey,
I like to point when I boogie.

11:57.818 --> 11:59.452
Show people where I'm going.

11:59.486 --> 12:01.889
Okay.
I can't tell her the truth.

12:01.922 --> 12:04.524
It would crush her.

12:04.557 --> 12:07.127
Honey, maybe you can read it
and tell her?

12:07.160 --> 12:08.228
No.

12:08.261 --> 12:09.562
Jessica and I
have an agreement

12:09.596 --> 12:11.865
to never comment on each
other's creative pursuits.

12:11.899 --> 12:14.034
As friends, it's better
to not know and wonder

12:14.067 --> 12:16.036
than to know and...know.

12:16.069 --> 12:17.637
Marvin, will you read it?

12:17.670 --> 12:19.272
No, sorry, buddy.
No.

12:19.306 --> 12:20.573
I don't read stories.

12:20.607 --> 12:22.910
I go out into the world,
and I make my own.

12:22.943 --> 12:25.212
Listen, this'll be okay.

12:25.245 --> 12:26.613
I know some people
who aren't afraid

12:26.646 --> 12:28.748
to tell Jessica
exactly what they think.

12:28.782 --> 12:29.883
Your book is not good.

12:29.917 --> 12:31.584
It didn't make
any sense.

12:31.618 --> 12:33.253
I liked the robot?

12:33.286 --> 12:35.789
You're not supposed
to like the robot!

12:35.823 --> 12:37.791
So none of you
were thrilled

12:37.825 --> 12:39.292
with the twists
and the turns in the book?

12:39.326 --> 12:40.460
I hated it.
Boo.

12:40.493 --> 12:41.929
It made me sad
for some reason.

12:41.962 --> 12:44.464
I see.

12:44.497 --> 12:46.633
Okay, well, thank you
for your honesty.

12:46.666 --> 12:48.335
Would you mind
leaving me your manuscripts

12:48.368 --> 12:50.270
so I can look through
your individual notes?

12:50.303 --> 12:51.571
Yeah. Absolutely.
Sure.

12:51.604 --> 12:52.840
Here you go.

12:52.873 --> 12:55.342
I can't believe
those women!

12:55.375 --> 12:58.846
I know, but suburban housewives
are your target demo.

12:58.879 --> 13:00.247
Better to get
their feedback now

13:00.280 --> 13:01.314
so you can start rewriting.

13:01.348 --> 13:03.250
I am not gonna change
a word!

13:03.283 --> 13:04.952
Who cares what they think?!

13:04.985 --> 13:06.086
You loved it, right?

13:06.119 --> 13:08.421
Um...yes.

13:08.455 --> 13:10.323
Those wet hens
are just jealous.

13:10.357 --> 13:12.592
Privileged white women
who can't stand

13:12.625 --> 13:14.661
to see me rising
like a phoenix

13:14.694 --> 13:16.696
out of the ashes
of this cul-de-sac!

13:17.797 --> 13:21.668
Tell Kenny about my struggle
before you give this to him.

13:21.701 --> 13:26.506
**

13:26.539 --> 13:28.541
Hi. Uh -- Hmm.

13:28.575 --> 13:30.710
Howdy.

13:30.743 --> 13:33.646
Uh, hello, Mr. Rogers.

13:33.680 --> 13:35.315
Oh, sure.
I'll call you Kenny.

13:35.348 --> 13:36.816
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

13:36.850 --> 13:38.818
Uh...Kenny.
[ Chuckles ]

13:38.852 --> 13:40.120
Great to meet you.

13:40.153 --> 13:42.722
Speaking of great,
allow me to self-segue

13:42.755 --> 13:44.324
to the topic
of my wife's novel.

13:44.357 --> 13:46.193
I just heard Kenny's limo
is on its way from the airport.

13:46.226 --> 13:47.194
[ Breathes deeply ]

13:47.227 --> 13:49.562
Word is,
he is dressed to the nines.

13:49.596 --> 13:51.564
Well, so am I.
I'm wearing my silver stud.

13:51.598 --> 13:53.967
Ah. I thought
that was a piece of glitter.

13:54.001 --> 13:56.203
No, no.
It's the happy-sad drama masks.

13:58.105 --> 13:59.739
Ah, that's fun.

13:59.772 --> 14:03.810
[ Hip-hop music plays ]

14:03.843 --> 14:05.412
[ Music ends, disc changes ]

14:05.445 --> 14:06.479
[ Click ]

14:06.513 --> 14:08.181
[ Fife playing ]

14:08.215 --> 14:09.482
Man:
"Dearest Henrietta,

14:09.516 --> 14:11.484
I write from the snowy hills
of Valley Forge

14:11.518 --> 14:12.652
as we await word
from the front.

14:12.685 --> 14:14.054
Not this again.

14:14.087 --> 14:16.023
I know you don't understand
how I could leave you

14:16.056 --> 14:17.857
and our son Gideon
so far away,

14:17.891 --> 14:20.393
but I fight not only
for our family,

14:20.427 --> 14:22.562
but for something larger.

14:22.595 --> 14:24.764
Like what?
I fight because one person

14:24.797 --> 14:27.334
cannot impose their
singular will on the people.

14:27.367 --> 14:28.535
For to live in a land

14:28.568 --> 14:30.603
and not have a voice
in what transpires there

14:30.637 --> 14:35.075
is to live not under a song
of freedom, but of tyranny."

14:35.108 --> 14:36.910
Evan:
Powerful stuff, isn't it?

14:36.944 --> 14:38.778
Wait till the part
where the flag was still there.

14:38.811 --> 14:40.447
Tears. Full tears.

14:40.480 --> 14:42.215
You're a lot like King George,
you know.

14:42.249 --> 14:45.252
I'm picturing rich guy,
well-fed,

14:45.285 --> 14:46.786
does whatever he wants.

14:46.819 --> 14:48.055
Yeah, I can see it.

14:48.088 --> 14:49.622
No, he was a bad king.

14:49.656 --> 14:52.259
A tyrant.
Imposing his will on the people.

14:52.292 --> 14:54.127
Well, I'm not trying
to be a tyrant.

14:54.161 --> 14:57.230
It's just...music
has always been my thing.

14:57.264 --> 14:58.631
And my friends know that.

14:58.665 --> 14:59.933
That was before.

14:59.967 --> 15:02.535
That 300-disc changer
is the New World.

15:02.569 --> 15:04.437
It shuffles
more than just songs, Eddie.

15:04.471 --> 15:06.406
It shuffles expectations.

15:06.439 --> 15:09.209
One of the original tenets
of our republic was,

15:09.242 --> 15:11.711
"No taxation
without representation."

15:11.744 --> 15:13.947
Your friends helped pay
for the carousel, Eddie.

15:13.981 --> 15:16.116
Now they want a say
in what it plays.

15:16.149 --> 15:17.985
Wow.

15:18.018 --> 15:21.388
Y'all just turned
my bedroom into school.
[ Chuckles ]

15:21.421 --> 15:23.123
Man: [ High-pitched voice ]
* Happy birthday, Evan *

15:23.156 --> 15:24.224
* Happy birthday, Evan *

15:24.257 --> 15:25.492
* Happy birthday, Evan *

15:25.525 --> 15:27.060
* Come back to Chuck E. Cheese *

15:27.094 --> 15:28.461
* Happy birthday, Evan *

15:28.495 --> 15:29.462
* Happy birthday, Evan *

15:29.496 --> 15:31.298
That was
a great 8th birthday.

15:31.331 --> 15:33.300
**

15:33.333 --> 15:34.834
Pleasure to meet you,
Louis.

15:34.867 --> 15:36.103
Keep up the good work.

15:36.136 --> 15:37.304
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you, Kenny.

15:37.337 --> 15:38.838
And may I just say,
you killed it

15:38.871 --> 15:40.840
on that episode
of "Dr. Quinn, Medicine Woman."

15:40.873 --> 15:42.609
[ Chuckles ]
Believable cough, wasn't it?

15:42.642 --> 15:43.643
[ Both laugh ]

15:43.676 --> 15:45.979
All right, Kenny.

15:46.013 --> 15:48.915
**

15:48.948 --> 15:50.283
Whew!

15:52.819 --> 15:54.954
Oh, that man
is a class act.

15:54.988 --> 15:56.289
And look at the gift
he brought me.

15:56.323 --> 15:57.524
Rattlesnake boots.

15:57.557 --> 15:58.791
My favorite snake!

15:58.825 --> 16:01.261
It's pretty amazing
how an animal with no feet

16:01.294 --> 16:02.695
can be reborn
as footwear.

16:02.729 --> 16:03.930
Huh.

16:03.963 --> 16:05.332
Louis!

16:05.365 --> 16:06.699
Did you give Kenny
that envelope?

16:06.733 --> 16:08.635
Oh. I did.

16:08.668 --> 16:09.836
He read a couple pages,

16:09.869 --> 16:11.138
said crime novels
weren't his thing,

16:11.171 --> 16:12.472
and gave it back to me.

16:12.505 --> 16:15.008
I'm sorry.
We gave it a good try.

16:15.042 --> 16:18.145
Help me understand how he read
a couple of pages

16:18.178 --> 16:20.513
if my book
was not in the envelope.

16:20.547 --> 16:22.882
What do you mean?

16:22.915 --> 16:26.619
You handed Kenny
the instruction manual

16:26.653 --> 16:31.458
to our broken coffee maker
and my 20-page complaint letter.

16:31.491 --> 16:34.861
This is my manuscript.

16:34.894 --> 16:37.030
**

16:40.767 --> 16:41.901
I don't understand.

16:41.934 --> 16:43.170
Why did you give me
the coffee-maker letter?

16:43.203 --> 16:44.304
It was an accident!

16:44.337 --> 16:45.972
While it is
very well-written,

16:46.005 --> 16:48.041
it's not what I wanted Kenny
to publish.

16:48.075 --> 16:50.677
Next time you ask me to ask
my boss for a huge favor,

16:50.710 --> 16:52.379
please make sure
you give me the right envelope.

16:52.412 --> 16:55.048
You did not even give it
to him!

16:55.082 --> 16:57.717
All right,
all right, listen.

16:57.750 --> 16:59.219
The truth is...

16:59.252 --> 17:00.653
I did not like your book.

17:00.687 --> 17:03.156
I know.
You said you loved it.

17:03.190 --> 17:05.825
No, I love you, and I didn't
want to hurt your feelings.

17:05.858 --> 17:07.827
I'm sorry. I should have
been honest sooner.

17:07.860 --> 17:10.763
But I can't vouch for something
that I don't believe in.

17:10.797 --> 17:14.701
You think I always believed
in this place?!

17:14.734 --> 17:16.903
I know you didn't feel good
about the original carpeting.

17:16.936 --> 17:19.106
Everyone in our family
thought you were crazy

17:19.139 --> 17:21.241
for moving us here,
but I supported you.

17:21.274 --> 17:23.676
Jessica, there is
a character in your book

17:23.710 --> 17:25.945
that somehow manages
to get murdered twice.

17:25.978 --> 17:27.614
It --
It doesn't make any sense.

17:27.647 --> 17:28.848
And a Chinese immigrant

17:28.881 --> 17:30.883
opening up
a Western-themed steakhouse

17:30.917 --> 17:32.685
in Central Florida does?

17:32.719 --> 17:37.290
It doesn't matter that your idea
didn't make sense to me.

17:37.324 --> 17:38.791
It made sense to you.

17:38.825 --> 17:41.461
It was your dream,
and that's enough for me.

17:41.494 --> 17:43.863
[ Sighs ]

17:43.896 --> 17:46.766
Well, now I know the title
of my next book --

17:46.799 --> 17:49.369
"A Case
of a Knife to the Back."

17:49.402 --> 17:50.803
[ Sighs ]

17:50.837 --> 17:53.306
[ Door opens ]
Je--

17:53.340 --> 17:54.374
[ Door closes ]

17:54.407 --> 17:55.642
Dude, you're crazy.

17:55.675 --> 17:57.777
I'm telling you.
She's beautiful.

17:57.810 --> 18:00.947
Fox Maid Marian
from the "Robin Hood" cartoon?

18:00.980 --> 18:02.081
Rent it again.

18:02.115 --> 18:04.050
And really look at her.

18:04.083 --> 18:06.286
She's so modest
and elegant.

18:06.319 --> 18:08.988
I did like it
when she played badminton.

18:12.825 --> 18:16.062
Was that just...

18:16.095 --> 18:18.698
Um, Eddie,
what are you...

18:28.608 --> 18:31.878
Just six more wires, guys.

18:33.146 --> 18:36.349
I got to start respecting
roadies, man.

18:40.787 --> 18:43.556
From now on,
we each have an equal say.

18:45.158 --> 18:46.659
Cool of you to say that.

18:46.693 --> 18:48.928
I appreciate
you coming around on Enya.

18:48.961 --> 18:50.697
Here's the thing, Dave --

18:50.730 --> 18:51.931
I think Enya sucks.

18:51.964 --> 18:53.433
But you like her,

18:53.466 --> 18:56.369
so she deserves a place
in the carousel.

18:56.403 --> 18:58.205
Democracy.
Democracy.

18:58.238 --> 18:59.706
Together: Democracy.

19:01.674 --> 19:04.043
[ Heavy-metal music plays ]

19:04.076 --> 19:05.312
Gwar!

19:05.345 --> 19:06.713
Who hurt these people?

19:06.746 --> 19:08.114
What do their mothers think?

19:08.147 --> 19:10.383
Gwar has no mothers!

19:13.986 --> 19:18.291
**

19:18.325 --> 19:20.227
If this is another one
of your political cartoons,

19:20.260 --> 19:21.394
I don't want to read it.

19:21.428 --> 19:22.729
It's not.

19:25.164 --> 19:26.799
[ Sighs ]

19:26.833 --> 19:28.501
"Dear Kenny,
I know we've only just met,

19:28.535 --> 19:32.171
but I'm writing on behalf
of my wife, Jessica.

19:32.205 --> 19:33.406
She's finished a novel,

19:33.440 --> 19:36.543
which I'm hoping you'll read
and share with your agent.

19:36.576 --> 19:38.645
As with everything she does,

19:38.678 --> 19:42.014
she put her heart and soul
into it.

19:42.048 --> 19:44.517
Thank you
for considering it.

19:44.551 --> 19:47.086
Your partner in cattle
and cluck, Louis Huang."

19:47.119 --> 19:49.722
I'm sorry I lied about
giving him your book

19:49.756 --> 19:51.824
and for not being honest
about how I felt.

19:51.858 --> 19:54.761
I always want you
to be honest with me.

19:54.794 --> 19:56.829
Even if you think
I'm not gonna like it.

19:56.863 --> 19:58.331
I will be.
I promise.

19:58.365 --> 20:00.567
And you don't have
to send him this letter.

20:00.600 --> 20:01.834
I absolutely do.

20:01.868 --> 20:03.336
I should have supported you
from the beginning.

20:03.370 --> 20:05.772
You should wait until I write
a book that you believe in.

20:05.805 --> 20:08.207
I may not believe
in the detective abilities

20:08.241 --> 20:09.609
of Jennifer Hong.

20:09.642 --> 20:13.079
But I will always believe
in the dreams of Jessica Huang.

20:16.316 --> 20:18.285
Why isn't that sentence
in the letter?

20:18.318 --> 20:20.086
I'll add it
and send it out with your book.

20:20.119 --> 20:21.854
Perfect.
[ Chuckles ]

20:21.888 --> 20:23.956
Are you wearing
a silver stud?

20:23.990 --> 20:25.925
Oh, yeah, yeah.
What do you think?

20:25.958 --> 20:27.794
Oh, I...

20:27.827 --> 20:30.463
I love it.
It's amazing.

20:30.497 --> 20:32.965
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, thanks.

20:32.999 --> 20:35.234
Yeah, I love it, too.

20:39.171 --> 20:43.410
**

20:43.443 --> 20:45.111
Hissssss!

20:45.144 --> 20:46.145
[ Door closes ]

20:46.178 --> 20:47.947
Louis, he responded.

20:49.416 --> 20:50.983
Oh, wow.
Okay.

20:51.017 --> 20:52.285
No matter
what the letter says,

20:52.319 --> 20:54.086
just remember it's
only one person's opinion.

20:54.120 --> 20:56.255
Okay.

20:56.289 --> 20:57.557
"Dear Jessica,

20:57.590 --> 20:59.592
as you probably know
from reading 'The Gift,'

20:59.626 --> 21:01.127
I sure do love a mystery.

21:01.160 --> 21:03.796
And, boy, did yours have me
by the throat...

21:03.830 --> 21:06.165
or in this case,
the brain -- Get it?"

21:06.198 --> 21:07.900
Oh, my God! He loved it!
He loved it!

21:07.934 --> 21:09.969
"My agent and I
will be in touch soon!

21:10.002 --> 21:12.138
Oh, and thank Louis
for the pen.

21:12.171 --> 21:14.073
Smoothest write
of my damn life.

21:14.106 --> 21:16.409
I think she's got
a couple of songs in her."

21:16.443 --> 21:17.744
[ Gasps ]

21:17.777 --> 21:19.512
Do you realize
what this means?

21:19.546 --> 21:20.780
I might be published!
He loved the pen!

21:20.813 --> 21:22.649
You might be published!
[ Squeals ]

21:22.682 --> 21:24.150
Also, you were wrong!

21:24.183 --> 21:26.386
Take the win.
Books are subjective.
